uzuki Roshi's teachings are valuable not only for those with a general interest in Buddhism but also for students of Zen practice wanting an example of how a modern master in the Japanese Soto Zen tradition understands this core text today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aZen BuddhismxDoctrines. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / General (see also PHILOSOPHY / Buddhist).2bisacsh  a1970.  abeauty.  abuddhism.  abuddhist poetry.  abuddhist teachings.  abuddhists.  acollection of lectures.  aeastern philosophy.  ajapan.  ajapanese buddhism.  alife journey.  ameditation instructions.  amodern buddhism.  anonfiction.  aoneness.  aphilosophy.  aquestion and answer.  areligious treatise.  asandokai.  asoto zen tradition.  aspiritual insight.  aspiritualism.  aspirituality and religion.  astudents and teachers.  awestern students.  aworld religions.  azen buddhism.  azen masters.  azen practices.  azen teachers.  azen.1 aWeitsman, Mel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeitsman, Mel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWenger, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWenger, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093623240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520936232423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520936232/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles